      "lesson title": "AI in Safety-Critical Transport Systems: What Can Go Wrong?",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how artificial intelligence is being used across safety-critical transport systems, including aviation, rail, and road vehicles, and what happens when things go wrong. Designed for beginners, it breaks down real-world examples of AI failures and near-misses to help you understand the practical risks involved. You will learn how errors in AI decision-making, sensor interpretation, and automated control systems can have serious consequences for passengers, crew, and cargo. The lesson also introduces key concepts around system reliability, human oversight, and the importance of fail-safe design in transport environments. By the end, you will have a clearer picture of why getting AI right in these settings is not just a technical challenge but a matter of public safety.",
